Dispatches from the cutting edge of flagellar biology, part 1 http://roughguidetoevolution.blogspot.com/2008/09/dispatches-from-cutting-edge-of.html Dispatches from the cutting edge of flagellar biology, part 2 http://roughguidetoevolution.blogspot.com/2008/09/dispatches-from-cutting-edge-of_17.html In 2003, Nick Matzke (then at the NCSE and so a couple of years later science adviser to the plaintiffs in the Dover trial) wrote an essay summarising plausible evolutionary scenarios for the origin of the bacterial flagellum.
